"'''Priority: X'''" is a short story written by [[George R. Strayton]], including illustrations by [[Chris Trevas]]), originally published in [[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 12|''Star Wars Galaxy Magazine'' 12]] by [[Topps]] in the summer of [[1997]]. It has since been released online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Hyperspace'']]. It takes place in [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]].

==Plot summary==
[[Hart-and-Parn Gorra-Fiolla]] (known as Fiolla) is returning from a mission on [[Ulicia]]. Fiolla is an executive with the [[Corporate Sector Authority/Legends|Corporate Sector Authority]] and she receives a priority X message from the office of the [[Prex]], [[Chils Meplin]]. She is ordered to track down a band of rebels in the [[Abo Dreth system/Legends|Abo Dreth system]]. During the trip to [[Abo Dreth]], Fiolla's [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]], [[Naven Crel]], grabs her [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]]. Fiolla turns the table and is able to re-secure Crel.

After they reach Abo Dreth, Fiolla and Crel are ambushed by a [[Gender/Legends|woman]] that turns out to be the Prex's assistant, [[Akeeli Somerce]]. Somerce is out to silence Crel and Fiolla. Crel saves Fiolla's life when Somerce fires, but [[Death/Legends|dies]] in the process. Fiolla discovers that Crel had gone undercover in search of a traitor to the CSA. His investigations had led him to the Prex. Fiolla vows to stop the Prex's [[Standard day/Legends|days]] of selling the CSA out to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].

